    "title": "Senior Plant Manager at Supreme Industries",
    "description": "Supreme Industries has an exciting opening for a Plant Manager at our Mysuru office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Supreme Industries:\nSupreme Industries is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Implement lean manufacturing and continuous improvement initiatives\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in FMEA\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Supreme Industries!",
